.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md:1:# create-feature-catalog
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-2-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-3-Create canonical feature-inventory packages for shipped systems, with a root catalog plus one source-anchored file per feature.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-4-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-5-## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-6-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md:7:`create-feature-catalog` is a nested workflow packet of the `sk-doc` parent hub. It authors canonical current-state feature inventories rooted at `feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md`, with category folders and one source-anchored per-feature file per root catalog entry. The root catalog stays inventory-first and navigation-focused; per-feature files carry the implementation truth, source anchors, and validation references. `SKILL.md` is the authoritative contract.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-8-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-9-## 2. WHEN TO USE
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-10-
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-12-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-13-Good fits:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-14-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md:15:- Creating or updating `feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md`
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-16-- Splitting a large feature surface into category folders
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-17-- Creating one stable per-feature file for each root catalog entry
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-18-- Capturing current shipped behavior with source-file and validation anchors
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-26-- `references/README.md` - route-map into the reference overflow, loaded before authoring or restructuring a catalog.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-27-- `references/examples.md` - annotated walkthrough of a shipped feature catalog (root-catalog and per-feature anatomy).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-28-- `references/common-pitfalls.md` - recurring catalog defects with worked fixes and the template-versus-reference split.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md:29:- `assets/feature-catalog/feature-catalog-template.md` - source scaffold for the root `feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md:30:- `assets/feature-catalog/feature-catalog-snippet-template.md` - scaffold for each per-feature reference file.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-31-- `changelog/.gitkeep` - placeholder for packet changelog history.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-32-- No packet-local `scripts/` directory is present; validation is consumed from the shared sk-doc backbone.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-33-
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-36-A catalog package uses this structure:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-37-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-38-```text
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md:39:feature-catalog/
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md:40:├── feature-catalog.md
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-41-├── category-name/
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-42-│   ├── feature-name.md
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-43-│   └── another-feature-name.md
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-45-    └── feature-name.md
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-46-```
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-47-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md:48:Category folders use descriptive kebab-case names such as `category-name`; the root catalog `feature-catalog.md` owns display order, not the folder name.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-49-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-50-Per-feature files use stable `feature-name.md` slugs without numeric prefixes.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-51-
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-54-## 5. QUICK START
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-55-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-56-```text
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md:57:/create:feature-catalog for the MCP memory tools
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-58-```
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-59-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-60-Then follow the packet flow:
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-62-1. Read the target system docs, source files, commands, tests, and existing README material.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-63-2. Load `references/README.md`, which routes to the worked example and pitfalls references.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-64-3. Decide whether the feature surface is large enough to warrant a catalog.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md:65:4. Create the root catalog from `assets/feature-catalog/feature-catalog-template.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-66-5. Create one category folder per root section using the bare descriptive slug.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md:67:6. Create one per-feature file per root entry from `assets/feature-catalog/feature-catalog-snippet-template.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-68-7. Verify root-entry to feature-file parity, links, source anchors, and shipped-behavior claims.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-69-8. Run shared validation from `../shared/scripts/` before delivery.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-70-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md:71:The source templates retain their current underscore filenames until their separate source-file migration. Those source names are not emitted package names.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-72-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-73-## 6. HUB RELATIONSHIP
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/README.md-74-
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-1----
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:2:name: create-manual-testing-playbook
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-3-description: Author manual testing playbook packages with deterministic scenarios, evidence collection, and multi-agent execution planning.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-4-allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-5-version: 1.0.1.1
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-6----
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-7-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:8:<!-- Keywords: manual testing playbook, testing playbook, deterministic scenario, evidence collection, operator validation, multi-agent execution, release readiness, create:manual-testing-playbook -->
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-9-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-10-# Manual Testing Playbook Creation
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-11-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:12:`create-manual-testing-playbook` is the manual-validation package workflow for the `sk-doc` family. It authors `manual-testing-playbook/` packages for skills and systems that need reproducible operator-facing scenarios, evidence capture, release-readiness review, and realistic orchestration or multi-agent execution planning.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-13-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-14-Core principle: keep shared rules in the root playbook, keep execution truth in per-feature files, and make every scenario deterministic enough that another operator can reproduce the verdict.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-15-
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-21-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-22-Use this workflow when the request involves:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-23-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:24:- `/create:manual-testing-playbook`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:25:- Creating `manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-26-- Building one-file-per-feature manual test scenarios.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-27-- Designing deterministic prompts, command sequences, expected signals, evidence, pass/fail criteria, and failure triage.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-28-- Planning manual validation across multiple operators, agents, CLIs, MCP tools, or runtime surfaces.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-29-- Converting an ad hoc release checklist into a reusable evidence-driven playbook package.
