.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-231-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-232-1. **Confirm the promotion gate.** Read the source packet `decision-record.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, and benchmark evidence. Confirm an accepted decision, stable headline, stable fixture, replay commands, and a defensible winner or explicit provisional status.
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-238-7. **Write `benchmark-report.md`.** Use the ten-section structure from this SKILL and the report template. Generalize the headline and state the load-bearing insight separately from the headline winner when the data shows a non-obvious cause.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-239-8. **Write `source.md`.** Use the source template. Include the spec packet path, per-file navigation map, evidence map, follow-on notes, and last-updated date.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-240-9. **Update the README index row.** Add or update the row with date, folder link, winner or status, headline metric, and source packet path.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:241:10. **Validate authored markdown.** Run `python3 .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/scripts/validate_document.py --type readme <file>` on `benchmark-report.md` and `benchmarks/README.md`. Fix blocking issues before delivery.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-242-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-243-### Authoring Order Rules
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-244-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-245-- Stabilize the headline and section structure before polishing prose.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-246-- Write the load-bearing insight and caveats before recommendations.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:247:- Validate before adding or finalizing the README index row.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-248-- Keep raw evidence out of the report; curate and link through `source.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-249-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-250-### Artifact Sources
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-270-5. **PROCESS NOTES**: what was tried, what failed, and why.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-271-6. **FINDINGS**: unique wins, universal floor and ceiling, mismatch analysis, and load-bearing insight.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-272-7. **CAVEATS**: single-run signal, fixture limits, stack-level confounds, schema migration cost, reranker/runtime confounds.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:273:8. **RECOMMENDATIONS**: Tier 1 apply now, Tier 2 validate first, Tier 3 future.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-274-9. **REPRODUCIBILITY**: exact replay commands plus expected wall-clock.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-275-10. **CROSS-LINKS**: sibling MCP benchmarks, authoritative spec packet, follow-on packets.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-276-
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-279-### Report Style
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-280-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-281-- Write with the same care as a sk-doc skill reference.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:282:- Include frontmatter appropriate for a reference document.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-283-- Use H2 numbered headers with ALL CAPS section names.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-284-- Use tables for data and fenced code blocks for verbatim commands.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-285-- Keep slugs and anchors stable across revisions.
--
