.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-451-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-452-## 10. SKILL-BENCHMARK STORAGE AND INDEX
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-453-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:454:A skill-benchmark measures whether a skill is well-routed, discoverable, efficient, and useful; it is run by the deep-improvement Lane C harness (`/deep:skill-benchmark`), which emits a JSON+Markdown report pair per run. This packet owns exactly two things: the **storage convention** for a hub's `benchmark/` tree and the **template for its `benchmark/README.md` index**. It never authors the per-run report, the runner, or the scoring (see ALWAYS / NEVER). The full storage convention, run-label naming, and renderer boundary live in [`references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md`](references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md); the D1-D5 contract stays lane-local, cross-linked and never restated.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-455-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-456-### Storage Shape
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-457-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:458:A benchmarked skill or hub carries a `benchmark/` tree; every run writes its report pair into its own `<run-label>/` sibling folder:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-459-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-460-```text
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-461-<skill-or-hub>/benchmark/
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-462-├── README.md              # optional hub index — templated here
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-463-├── baseline/              # FROZEN comparison anchor — never regenerated
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:464:│   ├── skill-benchmark-report.json
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:465:│   └── skill-benchmark-report.md   # renderer-owned render
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:466:├── <run-label>/           # one Lane C run; sibling to every other run
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:467:│   ├── skill-benchmark-report.json
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:468:│   └── skill-benchmark-report.md
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-469-└── fixtures/              # optional INPUT corpus — not a run
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-470-```
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-471-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-472-Runs are siblings; one never overwrites another. `baseline/` is the frozen before-snapshot, never re-run in place — a new run is always a new sibling folder.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-473-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:474:Every new `<run-label>` must match `^[a-z0-9]+(?:-[a-z0-9]+)*$`. Reject underscore-bearing or ambiguous labels instead of rewriting them after a run path has been selected. Existing legacy run folders remain historical references until their owning migration phase renames them.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-475-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-476-### Templates
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-477-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-478-| Output file | Template |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-479-| --- | --- |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-480-| `<skill-or-hub>/benchmark/README.md` | [`assets/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-readme-template.md`](assets/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-readme-template.md) |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:481:| `skill-benchmark-report.md` | None — renderer-owned; see NEVER below |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-482-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-483-### Authoring Workflow
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-484-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:485:1. **Read the storage guide** — confirm the run-label naming convention and the frozen-baseline rule.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-486-2. **Confirm the target** has (or is establishing) a Lane C `benchmark/` tree beside the skill it measures.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:487:3. **Author the index** from the README template: the run-label table (one row per on-disk folder, newest first), the structure map, re-run commands, and cross-links to the scoring contract and `/deep:skill-benchmark`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-488-4. **Cross-link the lane authorities** (`scoring-contract.md`, `operator-guide.md`); never restate the rubric or thresholds.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:489:5. **Validate** the README with the shared sk-doc validator.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-490-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-491-### ✅ ALWAYS / ⛔ NEVER (skill-benchmark)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-492-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:493:- **ALWAYS** keep the README run-label index in exact sync with the folders on disk — one row per folder.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:494:- **ALWAYS** add a new run as a fresh sibling run-label folder and index row; keep `baseline/` frozen.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-495-- **ALWAYS** cross-link the deep-improvement D1-D5 scoring contract; rubric, buckets, and thresholds are lane-owned.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:496:- **NEVER** hand-author or hand-edit `skill-benchmark-report.md` — it is an anti-drift render produced by `build-report.cjs` from the run JSON, silently overwritten on the next run.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-497-- **NEVER** author a fill-in template for that report; templates here are for the `benchmark/README.md` index and INPUT fixtures/profiles only.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-498-- **NEVER** copy the D1-D5 scoring, reviewer schema, or any scorer/runner into this packet — they are lane-local.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-499-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-500-### Success Criteria (skill-benchmark)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-501-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-502-- The skill or hub has a `benchmark/` tree following the convention, with a `baseline/` anchor and one sibling folder per run.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:503:- `benchmark/README.md` indexes every run-label folder, links the scoring contract and command, and carries no hand-authored report `.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:504:- Each run folder's `skill-benchmark-report.md` was produced by the renderer, not by hand.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-505-- Shared sk-doc validation passes for the README, or the remaining issue is escalated with exact command output.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-506-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-507----
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-522-    └── <profile>.json
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-523-```
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-524-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:525:A fixture is detected by its **shape**, not its filename; three families each feed a different scorer:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-526-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-527-| Fixture family | Shape marker | Oracle |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-528-| --- | --- | --- |
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-538-| Pattern / capability or reviewer-prompt fixture `<slug>.json` | [`assets/model-benchmark/model-benchmark-pattern-fixture-template.md`](assets/model-benchmark/model-benchmark-pattern-fixture-template.md) |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-539-| Run profile `<profile>.json` | [`assets/model-benchmark/model-benchmark-profile-template.md`](assets/model-benchmark/model-benchmark-profile-template.md) |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-540-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:541:Each template's fenced json block is the only thing copied into the shipped `.json`; shipped fixtures and profiles carry no frontmatter and no comments.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-542-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-543-### Authoring Workflow
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-544-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-545-1. **Pick the family and shape** and copy the closest existing fixture.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-546-2. **Author a code-task oracle** by generating every `tests[]` / `hidden_tests[]` value from a verified reference implementation — never hand-guess an oracle; bias hidden cases to held-out adversarial inputs.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-547-3. **Author a reviewer-prompt fixture** against the lane-local `reviewer-schema.md`; keep `expectedFindings` token-specific.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md:548:4. **Add or extend a profile** referencing the fixture `id` (code-task or pattern/capability), with a `scorer` matching the fixture shape plus the sweep matrix, sampling, and gate. A reviewer-mode profile (`mode: reviewer`, e.g. the shipped `reviewer-regression.json`) is a SEPARATE gated lane family (`SPECKIT_REVIEWER_BENCHMARKS`) that `profile-validator.cjs` does not validate — it is authored in-lane, not through this scaffold; the packet only records that it exists as a distinct reviewer input.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-549-5. **Parse every fixture and profile as JSON**, then hand off to the lane to dispatch, score, and file the evidence.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-550-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/SKILL.md-551-### ✅ ALWAYS / ⛔ NEVER (model-benchmark)
--
