.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md-12-## What Added
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md-13-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md-14-- **`assets/behavior-benchmark/behavior-benchmark-index-template.md`** — fillable scaffold for a `behavior_benchmark.md` package index (OVERVIEW with a declared-extensions subsection, SCENARIO TABLE, AXIS COVERAGE, EXECUTION, RELATED RESOURCES).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:15:- **`assets/behavior-benchmark/behavior-benchmark-scenario-template.md`** — fillable scaffold for one `<PREFIX>-NNN-<slug>.md` scenario contract: the runner-parsed JSON machine contract plus Rationale / Pass shape / Failure modes prose. The shipped scenario carries no frontmatter and no OVERVIEW heading; the template's own frontmatter, usage comment, and Overview are stripped on copy.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md-16-- **`assets/behavior-benchmark/behavior-benchmark-baseline-template.md`** — fillable scaffold for `baselines/claude-baseline.md` (Overview, Baseline Table, Capture Provenance, Notes), shipping `pending` / `not_captured` cells until a real Claude leg lands.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md-17-- **`references/behavior-benchmark/behavior-benchmark-guide.md`** — end-to-end authoring guide: what a behavior benchmark measures, how it differs from MCP promotion, package layout, naming conventions, the eight-step authoring workflow, scenario-matrix design rules, and validation.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md-18-- **`SKILL.md` §8 BEHAVIOR BENCHMARK PACKAGES** — the in-contract summary of the new family: package shape, template map, authoring workflow, naming, and its own ALWAYS/NEVER plus success criteria. §1 gains a Benchmark Families router table and behavior activation and keyword triggers; the description, keywords, and Family Boundary now cover both families.
--
