.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-9-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-10-The two new authored families:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-11-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:12:- **Skill-benchmark (Lane C)** — this packet owns the *storage convention* for a hub's `benchmark/` tree and the *template for its `benchmark/README.md` run-label index*. The per-run `skill-benchmark-report.md` is a `build-report.cjs` anti-drift render and is never hand-authored or templated; the D1-D5 scoring contract stays lane-local in deep-improvement and is cross-linked.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-13-- **Model-benchmark (Lane B)** — this packet owns the *input fixtures* the model under test answers (code-task oracle, pattern/capability evidence contract, reviewer-prompt) and the *run profiles* that drive a run. The evaluator, scorers, and reviewer-verdict contract stay lane-local in deep-improvement and are cross-linked.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-14-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-15-Lane A (agent-improvement) is named in Smart Routing only for disambiguation — its artifacts are code-owned and run entirely in-lane, so this packet ships no template, guide, or index for it (a documented non-goal).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-16-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-17-## What Added
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-18-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:19:- **`references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md`** — storage-and-naming standard for a hub `benchmark/` tree: sibling run-label folders, the frozen `baseline/` anchor, what lands in each run-label dir, and the hard boundary that the report `.md` is renderer-owned. The D1-D5 measurement contract is cross-linked, never restated.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:20:- **`assets/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-readme-template.md`** — fillable scaffold for a hub `benchmark/README.md` run-label index. It templates the index of runs only, never the rendered per-run report.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-21-- **`references/model-benchmark/model-benchmark-fixture-guide.md`** — authoring guide for Lane B inputs: the three fixture families and their shape markers, the profile shape and sweep keys, the reviewer-fixture shape at a glance, and the lane boundary for scoring.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-22-- **`assets/model-benchmark/model-benchmark-code-task-fixture-template.md`** — scaffold for one tiered code-task oracle fixture (`fn_name` + `tests[]` + `hidden_tests[]`); oracle values come from a verified reference implementation.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-23-- **`assets/model-benchmark/model-benchmark-pattern-fixture-template.md`** — scaffold for the two non-code-task shapes: the pattern evidence-contract fixture and the reviewer-prompt capability fixture.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-24-- **`assets/model-benchmark/model-benchmark-profile-template.md`** — scaffold for a Lane B run profile (fixtures, models, frameworks, scoring, sampling, gate) authored against the lane's profile validator.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:25:- **`SKILL.md` §10 SKILL-BENCHMARK STORAGE AND INDEX and §11 MODEL-BENCHMARK FIXTURES AND PROFILES** — the in-contract summaries of the two new families, each mirroring §9's shape: what it is, package/artifact shape, template map, authoring workflow, ALWAYS/NEVER (including the renderer-owned and lane-local boundaries), and success criteria.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:26:- **`SKILL.md` §12 REFERENCES** — a new REFERENCES H2 routing to the packet's family guides and the lane-owned normative contracts (behavior framework, Lane C scoring contract and renderer, Lane B evaluator and reviewer schema).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-27-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-28-## What Changed
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-29-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md-30-- **Smart Routing header normalized.** The merged `## 1. WHEN TO USE + SMART_ROUTING` header was split into `## 1. WHEN TO USE` and `## 2. SMART ROUTING`, and the Benchmark Families table plus the routing/decision content moved under SMART ROUTING. The families table gained an OWNS-vs-ROUTES column covering all six families (four authored, two code-owned non-goals). All H2s were renumbered contiguously (MCP-promotion sections 2-7 → 3-8, behavior 8 → 9), and intra-file `section N` cross-refs were updated to match. The packet now passes `package_skill.py --check` (previously failed on the missing `SMART ROUTING` and `REFERENCES` sections).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:31:- **Frontmatter.** `version` bumped 1.1.0.0 → 1.2.0.0; the description and Keywords comment now cover all four authored families.
