.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md-46-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md-47-The bake-off compared five code-tuned embedders against an 18-pair paraphrased fixture. One skipped on Apple Silicon because of an xformers requirement. The leading candidate was ahead by two net pairs over the current default (four unique wins minus two unique losses). No promotion into a live skill shipped on May 18 because the lead was a single-run signal requiring a 3-run confirmation.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md-48-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md:49:**Why the format was applied anyway**: the bake-off shape mirrored the sibling text-embedder run so operators moving between the two would not have to relearn the layout. Format symmetry is a legitimate reason to author the folder even before a headline is confirmed — but a single-run signal keeps the run out of a live skill tree until it is validated. This run never cleared that bar, which is why it stayed archived.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md-50-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md-51-**What the folder had to carry**:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md-52-- A single-run signal caveat: on a small fixture, single-sample wins under the noise floor are easy to mistake for real progress.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md-53-- A reranker swap discovery: the original cross-encoder failed silently on Apple Silicon MPS, returning un-reranked candidates with no operator-visible signal. The bake-off swapped to a different reranker mid-validation. Any prior measurement on the same fixture has to be treated as "rerank effectively off" and is not comparable.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md-54-- A stack-mismatch warning: the Python sentence-transformers stack is incomparable with the Ollama stack in the sibling skill.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md-55-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md:56:**A sidecar file (`risk-analysis-rerank-nondeterminism.md`) carried the follow-on context** that did not fit inside the report's ten-section structure. This is the pattern for depth that does not fit the report shape: drop it next to `benchmark-report.md` as a focused sidecar with its own frontmatter and anchors.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md-57-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md-58-**Lesson**: Single-run signals warrant a Caveats line and a follow-on packet, not a promotion claim. Adopt the format even when the headline is provisional, but make the provisional status explicit.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/shared/case-studies.md-59-
