.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-382-## 7. RULES
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-383-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-384-### ✅ ALWAYS
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-385-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:386:1. Use `manual-testing-playbook.md` as the root file name.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-387-2. Put per-feature files in root-level category folders named with the bare descriptive slug.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-388-3. Keep one canonical per-feature file for each feature ID.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-389-4. Use exact prompts, exact command sequences, observable expected signals, captured evidence, and binary pass/fail criteria.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:390:5. Keep shared review, orchestration, and release-readiness rules in the root playbook.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-391-6. Link scenarios back to the matching feature catalog entry when a catalog exists.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-392-7. Explicitly document exceptions when no matching catalog entry exists.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-393-8. Mark destructive scenarios and include safe recovery expectations.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:394:9. Validate the root playbook and manually review per-feature files before delivery.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-395-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-396-### ⛔ NEVER
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-397-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-398-1. Create a `snippets/` subtree for canonical per-feature files.
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-401-4. Renumber published feature IDs just to remove gaps.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-402-5. Use packet-history or spec-phase references as scenario identity.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-403-6. Ship unsynchronized prompt fields.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-404-7. Add packet-local `graph-metadata.json`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:405:8. Add numeric prefixes to category folder names or per-feature filenames; the root playbook index owns display order and the per-feature `stage:` field owns benchmark tier.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-406-9. Never use underscores in category folder or per-feature filename path segments.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-407-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-408-### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-409-
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-419-## 8. SUCCESS CRITERIA
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-420-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-421-A `create-manual-testing-playbook` run is done when:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-422-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:423:- The package uses the canonical shape: root `manual-testing-playbook.md` plus kebab-case category folders of per-feature files, with no `snippets/` subtree and no separate `review_protocol.md` or `subagent_utilization_ledger.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-424-- Every feature ID maps to exactly one per-feature file, and no packet-local `graph-metadata.json` was added.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-425-- Every scenario is deterministic: exact prompt, exact command sequence, observable expected signals, captured evidence, and binary `PASS`/`FAIL`/`SKIP` verdicts.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-426-- Prompt fields are synchronized across the scenario contract, the execution table, and any root summary.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-427-- Destructive scenarios are marked and isolated with safe recovery expectations.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:428:- The root playbook passes shared `validate_document.py`, per-feature files are manually spot-checked, and any remaining manual scope is documented honestly.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-429-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-430----
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-431-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md-432-## 9. RESOURCES FOR DEEP DETAIL & REFERENCES
