.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-9-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-10-# Create Feature Catalog
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-11-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:12:`create-feature-catalog` is the feature-inventory workflow packet of the `sk-doc` parent hub. It authors canonical current-state catalogs rooted at `feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md`, with category folders and one per-feature reference file per root catalog entry.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-13-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:14:Feature catalogs are the canonical inventory for what a system does today. They organize capabilities by category, summarize current behavior in a root catalog, and link to per-feature files that carry implementation anchors, tests, and metadata.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-15-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:16:Core principle: use the root catalog for stable inventory and navigation, and use per-feature files for implementation truth and traceable source anchors.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-17-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-18-This packet owns `/create:feature-catalog`, its `references/` set (indexed by `references/README.md`), and `assets/`. It consumes shared sk-doc validation and writing standards from `../shared/`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-19-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-20----
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-25-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-26-Use this workflow when the request involves:
