.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-181-```
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-182-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-183-Invariants:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-184-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:185:- Root file is always `feature-catalog.md` in lowercase.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-186-- Category directories use descriptive kebab-case names such as `category-name` (no numeric prefix).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-187-- Per-feature files use kebab-case names such as `feature-name.md` without numeric prefixes.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-188-- One root entry maps to exactly one per-feature file.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-189-- Slugs should remain stable after publication.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:190:- Display order is owned by the root catalog index (`feature-catalog.md`), not the folder name.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:191:- Per-feature snippet order is defined by the root catalog listing order; filenames do not encode order.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-192-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-193-### Required Resources
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-194-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-195-Use these packet resources while authoring:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-196-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:197:- `assets/feature-catalog-template.md` for the root catalog scaffold.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-198-- `assets/feature-catalog-snippet-template.md` for each per-feature file.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-199-- `../shared/references/quick-reference.md` and `../shared/references/validation.md` before delivery.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-200-- `../shared/references/frontmatter-versioning.md` when checking frontmatter version fields.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-201-- `references/README.md` to route the reference overflow — [`examples.md`](references/examples.md) (worked live-catalog walkthrough) and [`common-pitfalls.md`](references/common-pitfalls.md) (deep-dive pitfalls, template-versus-reference split) — only for depth beyond this inline workflow.
--
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-211-1. Read the target system docs, source files, command surfaces, MCP tool lists, tests, and existing README material before drafting the catalog.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-212-2. Decide whether a catalog is warranted; use a README summary instead when the feature surface is small, complete, stable, or too volatile for a maintained catalog.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-213-3. Decide the category taxonomy before writing prose.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-214-4. Stabilize category names, feature names, and feature slugs before polishing descriptions.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:215:5. Create `feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md` from `assets/feature-catalog-template.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:216:6. Create one category folder per root section using a descriptive kebab-case slug such as `category-name`; the root catalog listing defines display order.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-217-7. Create one per-feature file for each root entry using `assets/feature-catalog-snippet-template.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-218-8. Write concise root summaries and link each feature to its per-feature file.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-219-9. Fill each per-feature `## 2. HOW IT WORKS` section with current behavior.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-220-10. Use plain prose for short `HOW IT WORKS` sections and H3 subheadings for sections longer than three paragraphs.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-221-11. Fill implementation source tables and validation or test anchor tables for every feature claim.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-222-12. Fill `## 4. SOURCE METADATA`, including group, canonical file path, and related references.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:223:13. Validate the root catalog and each per-feature leaf file with shared validation (see §7).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-224-14. Manually verify feature-file links, root-entry parity, source anchors, and current-state wording.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-225-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-226-Authoring order matters:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-227-
