.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-420-## 10. SUCCESS CRITERIA
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-421-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-422-The catalog package is complete when:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-423-
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:424:- The root catalog exists at `feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md` and was built from the packet template.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:425:- Category folders use descriptive kebab-case slugs with no numeric prefixes, and display order is owned by the root catalog index.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:426:- Every root entry links to exactly one per-feature file, and every per-feature file is represented in the root catalog.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-427-- Each per-feature file carries frontmatter with a stable title, description, at least three `trigger_phrases`, and a four-part version, plus source-file and validation or test anchors for every feature claim.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md-428-- Prose describes current shipped behavior from the caller or operator perspective, with any rollout or compatibility layer labeled explicitly.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:429:- Shared validation ran clean on the root catalog and each per-feature leaf, and cross-file links, source anchors, and root-entry-to-feature-file parity were verified by hand.
