.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/references/prompt-voice.md-39-| A human asks the AI directly in conversation ("Review this PR", "Commit my staged changes", "Why is this test flaky?", "Help me start OAuth"). | The actor IS an AI orchestrator delegating to another tool/AI/agent (cross-CLI delegation, multi-agent dispatch, agent handback). |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/references/prompt-voice.md-40-| Code review on a PR, commit/git workflows, bug fixes, code questions, preference questions. | Safety-refusal scenarios where role context determines behavior (e.g., "git safety reviewer" decides whether to refuse a `--no-verify`). |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/references/prompt-voice.md:41:| The scenario could plausibly originate from a Slack DM or a terminal prompt. | Internal validation contracts where the orchestrator IS the operator (e.g., "validation operator validates context retrieval"). |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/references/prompt-voice.md-42-| Default for ~70% of scenarios. | Default for ~30% of scenarios - most often in cli-* and orchestration-heavy playbooks. |
