codex
One new contract break is now clear: the standard per-scenario playbook template still emits legacy `expected_intent`/`expected_resources`, while the manifest-backed topology gate requires `expected_workflow_mode` plus typed `{workflow_mode, leaf_resource_id}` pairs. Without a template update and a strict topology check, newly authored compiled-routing scenarios can look valid yet never provide the typed oracle.
